description.plain:
Mariel Semonte Orr (November 4, 1987-June 5, 2022)
Atlanta rapper Trouble broke onto the national scene in 2011 with his debut mixtape December  17th. Since then he has steadily released a stream of mixtapes including most recently #Zaydidit, Skoob Fresh in 2015, and Skoobzilla in 2016.

In 2017 he was featured on the Billboard Hot 100 song “Key to the Streets” by YFN Lucci.

On June 5, 2022, Orr was shot in the chest during a home invasion of the Rockdale County apartment of a female companion. He was transported to a hospital, where he died at age 34.

songs.title: Ready

description.plain: Trouble uses the Shawty Fresh produced banger to state his preparedness for “ANYTHING” that may come at him in life. Whether it be opportunity or misfortune, Trouble can deal with it: he’s “Ready”.
